videos.headline: Hokies' Phillips makes leaping grab just shy of end zone
videos.description: Virginia Tech's Josh Jackson finds Cam Phillips at the 1-yard line for a 28-yard pickup.

videos.headline: WVU picked off deep in Hokie territory
videos.description: West Virginia quarterback Will Grier has his pass intercepted by Trevon Hill on fourth down.

videos.headline: Crawford breaks free for 42-yard scamper
videos.description: West Virginia's Justin Crawford finds a big hole and outruns the Virginia Tech defense for a huge gain.

videos.headline: Grier connects with Sills for first WVU TD of season
videos.description: Will Grier finds David Sills V in the front of the end zone for an 11-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: Phillips makes contested catch to put VT in red zone
videos.description: Hokie receiver Cam Phillips adjusts mid-route to complete an impressive 28-yard grab.

videos.headline: Hokie freshman QB uses his legs to score
videos.description: Virginia Tech quarterback Josh Jackson runs it in from 5 yards out for Virginia Tech's first touchdown of the season.

videos.headline: Coach Holgorsen: QB Grier 'knocked rust off' in first half
videos.description: West Virginia head coach Dana Holgorsen is confident his team will adjust in the second half after quarterback Will Grier saw his first game action in over a year.

videos.headline: Hokies head into half with the lead
videos.description: With less than 30 seconds on the clock in the first half, Josh Jackson runs the ball into the end zone for a 5-yard touchdown and a Virginia Teach lead. The Hokies lead the Mountaineers 10-7 at the half.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Hokies head into half with the lead) 2017/9/3 ESHEET

videos.headline: White makes diving catch for big WVU gain
videos.description: Ka'Raun White lays out to haul in Will Grier's pass for a 33-yard pickup.

videos.headline: McClease sheds defenders en route to Virginia Tech TD
videos.description: Deshawn McClease breaks multiple tackles and scores from 12 yards out.

videos.headline: Grier finds Sills again for Mountaineer TD
videos.description: Will Grier connects with David Sills V on a slant for a 10-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: Jackson connects with Phillips for long Hokie TD
videos.description: Josh Jackson finds an open Cam Phillips downfield for a 32-yard touchdown connection.

videos.headline: Grier airs it out on big WVU completion
videos.description: West Virginia quarterback Will Grier throws a deep ball to Gary Jennings who hauls it in for a 43-yard gain.

videos.headline: WVU's Jennings takes it to the house on 60-yard TD
videos.description: Gary Jennings receives a long pass from Will Grier and outruns the Virginia Tech defenders for a long 60-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: QB Jackson keeps it himself for huge Hokie gain
videos.description: Josh Jackson scrambles up the middle for a 46-yard run, getting tackled just shy of the end zone.

videos.headline: Virginia Tech's McMillian pounds it in
videos.description: Travon McMillian scores from 3 yards out to give the Hokies the lead.

videos.headline: WVU-VT breakdown: A rivalry rekindled
videos.description: The crew analyzes the exciting season opener between West Virginia and Virginia Tech.

videos.headline: Virginia Tech outlasts WVU in back-and-forth thriller
videos.description: In a game in which the teams continually traded scores, the Hokies break a fourth-quarter tie on Travon McMillian's touchdown run for a 31-24 win.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Virginia Tech outlasts WVU in back-and-forth thriller) 2017/09/03 ESHEET

videos.headline: VT, WVU will have impact in their conference races
videos.description: Brian Griese compliments the starting quarterbacks for both teams and expects them to each have a say in the ACC and Big 12.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Analysis (VT, WVU will have impact in their conference races) 2017/09/03 SVP SC

videos.headline: Virginia Tech takes top-25 tussle over WVU
videos.description: The No. 21 Hokies knock off the No. 22 Mountaineers, as freshman QB Josh Jackson stars with 235 passing yards and 101 rushing yards in his first start.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Virginia Tech takes top-25 tussle over WVU) 2017/09/03 ESHEET
